  FOUR secondary school students of Osun State have been taken into police custody for attacking and injuring Peace Corps members in two schools. The injured officials have been hospitalised. A statement by Commissioner for Education Folorunsbo Oladoyin on Monday said, “The four students were caught with dangerous weapons and charms with which they caused bodily injuries on Peace Corps members who are now hospitalised. They have been handed over to the police for possible prosecution.” The commissioner warned students not to allow disgruntled elements to infiltrate their ranks to disturb the peace.  